text: Giorgi Baramidze (, born January 5, 1968) is a Georgian politician who was Vice-Prime Minister of Georgia and State Minister for Euro-Atlantic Integration from 2004 to 2012. He was acting Prime Minister of Georgia from 16 to 22 November, 2007, ==Personal life== Baramidze speaks Georgian, English, Russian and French. He is married. Baramidze has one daughter, Ann. ==References== Category:1968 births Category:Prime Ministers of Georgia Category:Politicians from Tbilisi Category:Living people
